meta.description:
This IDN table is published on <https://github.com/dotse/IDN-ref-tables> where you can find the latest version, other tables and information concerning the purpose, creation and update of the tables.

## Language references
Wikipedia: "Japanese orthography", http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_alphabet
In "Omniglot" - the online encyclopedia of writing systems and languages, http://www.omniglot.com/writing/japanese.htm
## References for contextual rules
RFC 5891: "Internationalized Domain Names in Applications (IDNA): Protocol" (proposed standard), http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5891
RFC 5892: "The Unicode Code Points and Internationalized Domain Names for Applications (IDNA)" (proposed standard), http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5892
UAX#24 (Unicode Standard Annex #24), "Unicode Script Property", http://www.unicode.org/reports/tr24
Unicode Character Database "ScriptExtensions.txt", http://www.unicode.org/Public/7.0.0/ucd/ScriptExtensions.txt
## Code points requiring contextual rules
Code point Description of rule/Reference
U+002D Label must neither start nor end with U+002D. Label HYPHEN-MINUS must not have U+002D in both third and fourth position. RFC 5891 (sec 4.2.3.1)
U+3006 Label must also have some Han, Hiragana or Katakana IDEOGRAPHIC CLOSING MARK code point. UAX #24 (sec 1.3) + Unicode Character Database (ScriptExtensions.txt)
U+30FB Label must also have some Han, Hiragana or Katakana KATAKANA MIDDLE DOT code point. RFC 5892 (Appendix A. 7.)
U+30FC Label must also have some Hiragana or Katakana KATAKANA-HIRAGANA PROLONGED code point. UAX #24 (sec 1.3) + Unicode Character SOUND MARK Database (ScriptExtensions.txt)

union.name: japanese-code-point
union.comment: Any code point tagged as Han, Hiragana or Katakana

union.name: kata-hira-code-point
union.comment: Any code point tagged as Hiragana or Katakana

rule.name: hyphen-minus-disallowed
rule.comment: RFC5891 restrictions on placement of U+002D
no consecutive hyphens in third and fourth

rule.name: japanese-in-label
rule.comment: RFC5892 restrictions on use of Katakana middle dot

rule.name: kata-hira-in-label
rule.comment: RFC5892 restrictions on use of Katakane-Hiragana prolonged sound mark
